nauthors have conjectured that \\emph{small, $\\epsilon$ size data yields long\ntime solutions on the $\\epsilon^{-8}$ time-scale}. A third goal of this paper\nis to also prove this second conjecture for 1D quasilinear Schr\\\"{o}dinger\nflows.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 Jun 2023 11:37:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-06-02"}
